author: Jonathan Sawyer
title: Under Armour Reveals 3D-Printed ArchiTech Futurist Sneaker
text:
Visit the original post to see all 4 images from this gallery. 
Brand: Under Armour
Model: ArchiTech Futurist
Key Features: Mid-top design, dynamic lattice network for ample cushioning and support, SpeedForm technology on the upper, compression lace system.
Release Date: March 30, 2017
Price: $300 USD
Availability: You can look forward to Under Armour’s new 3D-printed ArchiTech Futurist arriving in limited quantities at select brand houses and UA.com .
Editor’s Notes: In following up on last year’s introduction of the 3D-printed ArchiTech sneaker , Under Armour is back with their latest 3D-printed variant, the ArchiTech Futurist. The mid-top iteration in turn features the same design cues as the initial ArchiTech model, which provides with enhanced cushioning and superior support.
